      "verification": {
        "verified": true,
        "reason": "valid",
        "payload": "tree 8cf02684192914d22e690007829fb1d3b37a39b1\nparent 18773145c1ce62b13f472f7fe3ca1599c22ea751\nauthor Alexander Shevtsov <randomlogin76@gmail.com> 1779397323 +0200\ncommitter Alexander Shevtsov <randomlogin76@gmail.com> 1779400084 +0200\n\nnet: wait validation queue on cfilter request\n\nCheck if the requested compact filter correspond to a recent block, if\nso we wait for validation queue finishes processing. This mitigates a\nrace condition when an alread-known block had not yet constructed\nfilters, but was already advertised.\n\nIntroduce `BaseIndex::MaybeWaitForBlockIndexed` to check whether the\nrequested block is in range of `CF_MAX_BLOCKS_AHEAD_RACE_WAIT=2` blocks\nwhich invokes `SyncWithValidationInterfaceQueue`.\n",
